AdaptFS

Building Instructions
---------------------

    $ svn co svn://wolverine.psc.edu/projects
    $ cd projects
    $ git clone https://github.com/pscedu/adaptfs
    $ cd adaptfs
    $ make build
    $ sudo make install

Examples
--------

  Bring AdaptFS online:

    # mount_adaptfs /adaptfs

  Load a visual human dataset and create three "spins".

    # adaptctl load /antonfs/scratch/awetzel/vvfs-volumes/$(
	)small_vh2_272_384_368.vol 272:384:368:1:3 \
	vh0/x/%x.ppm 272:1:1:1:3 \
	vh0/y/%y.ppm 1:384:1:1:3 \
	vh0/z/%z.ppm 1:1:368:1:3 \
	vh.so
